            "body": "> This need not be part of the first implementation, though; for that, stable and nightly are the only important tags and can be re-generated on every run.\n\nYes, that seems to be the much simpler approach. Don't want to call the generating workflow \"expensive\" per se: [current build workflow](https://github.com/neovim/neovim.github.io/actions) takes 1m30s. So ~double that wouldn't be too big of a problem.\n\nI'll go with generating the docs of `stable` and `nightly` on the fly for now then: GH actions efficiency can be achieved later.",
